The paper deals with mechanism design and approximation algorithms for submodular bidders, which are topics typically studied in the areas of game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic economics (cs.EC). The use of demand queries and the computational complexity of truthful mechanisms suggest a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses communication efficiency, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
